==English==
===Noun===
'''creationism''' (''uncountable'')

# The [[Catholic]] [[doctrine]] that each individual human [[soul]] is [[create]]d by God, as opposed to [[traducianism]]
# Any [[creation]] [[belief]], especially a belief that the origin of things is due to an event or process of creation brought about by the deliberate act of any divine agency, such as a [[Creator]] god.
# The creation beliefs of [[Judaism]], [[Christianity]] or [[Islam]].
# The [[theological]] controversy concerning the origin of the human species, and other living beings, and especially questioning in what sense if any the creating acts of God are considered a matter of historical fact
# The subject of a debate concerning origins and the findings of science, focused on the degree to which the theory of [[evolution]] is compatible with religious belief in the Creator.

